# NEON Sustainable Use License

Version 1.0

## Acceptance

By using the software, you agree to all of the terms and conditions below.

## Copyright License

The licensor grants you a non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide, non-sublicensable, non-transferable license to use, copy, distribute, make available, and prepare derivative works of the software, in each case subject to the limitations below.

## Limitations

You may use or modify the software only for your own internal business purposes or for non-commercial or personal use.

You may distribute the software or provide it to others only if you do so free of charge for non-commercial purposes.

You may not provide the software to third parties as a hosted or managed service, where the service provides users with access to any substantial set of the features or functionality of the software.

You may not move, change, disable, or circumvent the license key functionality in the software, and you may not remove or obscure any functionality in the software that is protected by the license key.

You may not alter, remove, or obscure any licensing, copyright, or other notices of the licensor in the software. Any use of the licensor's trademarks is subject to applicable law.

## Permitted Uses

The following uses are expressly permitted under this license:

**Internal Business Use**: You may deploy and use NEON within your organization for internal collaboration, communication, and business operations, regardless of the size of your organization.

**Personal and Non-Commercial Use**: You may use NEON for personal projects, education, research, or any non-commercial purpose.

**Consulting and Support Services**: You may provide consulting, implementation, training, customization, and support services related to NEON to third parties, and charge fees for such services.

**Custom Development**: You may develop custom integrations, plugins, extensions, and modifications to NEON for your own use or for clients as part of consulting services.

**Contribution**: You may contribute modifications, improvements, and extensions back to the NEON project.

## Prohibited Uses

The following uses are expressly prohibited under this license:

**Competing Hosted Service**: You may not offer NEON, or any derivative work of NEON, as a hosted service where users pay for access to NEON functionality. This includes offering NEON as a software-as-a-service (SaaS), platform-as-a-service (PaaS), or any similar hosted offering that competes with services offered by the licensor.

**White-Labeling for Sale**: You may not rebrand, white-label, or resell NEON or any derivative work as your own product or service for a fee.

**Embedding in Commercial Products**: You may not embed or include NEON as a component of a commercial product or service that you sell, unless you have obtained a separate commercial license from the licensor.

**Circumventing Restrictions**: You may not use technical means to circumvent, disable, or remove any license restrictions, usage limitations, or license key protections in the software.

## Patents

The licensor grants you a license, under any patent claims the licensor can license, or becomes able to license, to make, have made, use, sell, offer for sale, import, and have imported the software, in each case subject to the limitations and conditions in this license. This license does not cover any patent claims that you cause to be infringed by modifications or additions to the software.

## Fair Use and Fair Code

NEON is distributed under the fair-code model. Fair-code is not a software license itself, but describes a software model where:

- Software is generally free to use and can be distributed by anybody
- Source code is openly available
- Software can be extended by anybody in public and private communities
- Commercial use is restricted by the authors to ensure sustainability

This license is designed to allow maximum freedom for individual users, developers, and organizations while protecting the project from commercial exploitation that would undermine its sustainability.

## Contributions

If you contribute modifications, enhancements, or other changes to NEON, you agree that:

1. Your contributions are provided under this same license
2. You have the right to make such contributions
3. You grant the licensor a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, irrevocable license to use, reproduce, modify, display, perform, sublicense, and distribute your contributions

